    • Uses of CMObject in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Abilities.interfaces

      Subinterfaces of CMObject in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Abilities.interfaces 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  Ability
      The basic interface for all skills, spells, chants, prayers, and properties.
      interface  CraftorAbility
      This interface denotes an ability that also incidentally is capable of generating objects, usually items.
      interface  DiseaseAffect
      DiseaseAffect is an ability interface to denote those properties, affects, or Disease objects that act as curable physical diseases.
      interface  ExtendableAbility
      An ExtendableAbility is an ability/effect object that can be more easily extended in code at runtime using various methods that add internal pointers to coded solutions to it's external api.
      interface  HealthCondition
      HealthCondition is an ability interface to denote those properties, affects, or properties that mean something is wrong with you health-wise.
      interface  ItemCraftor
      This interface denotes an ability that also incidentally is capable of generating objects, usually items.
      interface  ItemTicker
      The interface for affects which cause an Item to rejuvenate after a particular amount of time.
      interface  Language
      A Language ability represents both the ability to understand one or more spoken or written languages, and the ability to speak one or more spoken languages.
      interface  LimbDamage
      An LimbDamage is a kind of ability that denotes missing, broken, or damaged body parts.
      interface  MendingSkill
      This interface denotes an ability that also incidentally is capable of mending objects, usually items or mobs.
      interface  Trap
      A trap is a kind of ability that behaves mostly like a property, in that it is not typically invoked as a skill, although there are skills that generate or make use of Trap abilities.
      interface  TriggeredAffect
      TriggeredAffect is an ability interface to denote those properties that are typically non-removable inherent attributes of the things they affect.

      An object to access and change fields representing the varias aspects of a MOB

      A class defining the characteristics of a clan government, and its membership.

      A class for the characteristics of a position within a clan government.

      A climate represents the entire weather pattern of an area It does most of the mundane things related to weather changes based on season, area, and other factors.
      interface  CMCommon
      A common interface for common classes.

      The core of event handling in CoffeeMud, a CMMsg represents an event that occurs.

      A CoffeeShop is an object for storing the inventory of a shopkeeper, banker, auctionhouse, merchant, or other object that implements the ShopKeeper interface for the purpose of selling goods and services.

      A CoffeeTableRow object represents a period of sustained statistics gathering.
      interface  Faction
      A Faction is an arbitrary numeric range, where different mobs/players can be within that range, if they have the faction at all.

      A simple utility for making HTTP requests, which is implemented as a builder-type object.
      interface  JournalEntry 
      interface  Law
      The Law interface defines an object containing the various infractions that are recognized for a given LegalObject, the officials that enforce the infractions, some guidelines on their behavior, and information their processes of enforcement.
      interface  LegalWarrant
      A LegalWarrant is an important object in the triad of LegalBehavior and Law objects, as a part of the CoffeeMud legal system.
      interface  Manufacturer
      A class for holding information about the manufacturer of electronics.
      interface  PhyStats
      The PhyStats interface is a state object that holds some basic information about just about every Physical object in the game.
      interface  PlayerAccount
      An interface for a base player account.
      interface  PlayerStats
      Accessible from any PC mob object, PlayerStats are the repository for all manner of player specific mob values.
      interface  Poll
      A Poll object manages the data and processes for all of the public and private voting polls available through the CoffeeMud POLL CREATE POLL, LIST POLLS, etc..
      interface  Quest
      A quest object manages the details and text for a single descriptive script that is scheduled and, when directed, spawns, creates, watches, shuts down, and cleans up the various objects, subsidiary quests, and existing objects modifications related to this Quest.
      interface  RoomnumberSet
      A class for holding CoffeeMud-style room IDs of the form AreaName#[NUMBER], for instance, Midgaard#3001 This class is totally awesome because it stores them in an efficient way (holding room ids 5-10 not as 5,6,7,8,9,10, but as 5,10), but sorts them for quick reads.
      interface  ScriptingEngine
      The interface for the main CoffeeMud scripting engine, which implements a scripting engine descended from the old mud codebases of the 90's usually called MOBPROG.
      interface  Session
      A Session object is the key interface between the internet user and their player MOB.
      interface  Social
      Although at one time a simple public variable object, the Social became an environmental when it became import to be able to pass it as a tool of a message for various purposes.
      interface  Tattoo
      Tattoos are arbitrary markers or flags.
      interface  TimeClock
      This interface represents more than a "Time Zone", but a complete calendar, a complete lunar cycle, and schedule for days and nights.

      Subinterfaces of CMObject in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Items.interfaces 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  Ammunition
      Class for ammunition items used in weapons that require ammunition
      interface  AmmunitionWeapon
      An interface for a weapon which does not work without ammunition, or which can potentially require ammunition.
      interface  Armor
      Interface for items which are complex wearables.
      interface  BoardableShip
      A Boardable Ship, which is an object that's boardable, rooms are attached to it so you can get in.
      interface  Book
      A book is a readable object that can usually be written to.
      interface  CagedAnimal
      Represents a MOB being stored as an Item, such as a mob in a cage, or a baby.
      interface  ClanItem
      Clan Items are variations on normal items that behave uniquely for members of clans.
      interface  Coins
      Coins are an item that represent a single coin, or a stack of dollar bills.
      interface  Computer
      A computer is a particular type of electronics panel that holds software, and has readers who monitor the messages this panel generates, as well as use the Type command to enter data into this panel's software.
      interface  Container
      A container is an item that contains other items, including other containers.
      interface  DeadBody
      Represents a player or monster corpse, dead body, a stiff.
      interface  DeckOfCards
      An interface for a deck of playing cards, like you'd use to play Gin or Poker or something.
      interface  DoorKey
      Represents a key-like thing that opens a door, or a chest, or anything else locked.
      interface  ElecPanel
      An interface for a particular kind of container that is invisible when closed, holds particular kinds of electrical gear, and allows some level of manipulation of the items inside.
      interface  Electronics
      Electronics are items that can be turned on and off before their interesting behavior or ability is available, which requires "power" to be operated, and has some capacitance for power that keeps it running for some dramatic amount of time while it is no longer receiving new power.
      interface  FalseLimb
      A False, or Fake Limb is an item that re-provides a wear location, and the personal functionality that goes with that limb, to someone who is missing that limb due to amputation.
      interface  Food
      The food interface is for items for items that can be targeted with the EAT command, and which provide nourishment that reduces hunger.
      interface  FuelConsumer
      An interface for an Electrical item that also consumes some other sort of fuel other than electrical power, if it consumes any electricity at all.
      interface  HandOfCards
      A hand of cards is a partial group of cards container, containing individual cards.
      interface  InnKey
      An InnKey is a door key that can fly back into the inventory of its shopkeeper when its time is up.
      interface  Item
      The interface for all common items, and as a base for RawMaterial, armor, weapons, etc.
      interface  Light
      A Light is an item that can emit light for some period of time.
      interface  MagicDust
      Magic Dust is itemized magic, like a potion or pill, except that it can be targeted at someone else, making malicious magic.
      interface  MiscMagic
      A MiscMagic item are magical items like Pills, Potions, Wands, Rings, Scrolls, Dust and so forth.
      interface  MusicalInstrument
      Musical instruments are typically used by Bard types to make their magic.
      interface  PackagedItems
      An interface for a large number of Items packaged into a single Item object.
      interface  Pill
      A pill is a item that bestows some magic when eaten.
      interface  PlayingCard
      A playing card is just what it sounds like - a card you can play card games with.
      interface  Potion
      A potion is an item that bestows some magic upong the drinker.
      interface  PowerGenerator
      An interface that combines both a PowerSource and and FuelConsumer to produce a Power Generator, or converter from fuel to electricity.
      interface  PowerSource
      An interface for an Electrical item that produces rather than consumes power, though it may consume something else to generate that power.
      interface  RawMaterial
      RawMaterial houses the complete list of raw resource types, which are used to specify Item materials, and the nature of raw resources.
      interface  Recipe
      A Recipe is a special readable item that, merely by having, adds to the recipes available to construction-type common skills, such as tailoring, weaponsmithing, etc.
      interface  RoomMap
      An item that, when read, shows you a graphical map of an area.
      interface  SailingShip
      A Sailing Ship, which is an object that's boardable, rooms are attached to it so you can get in, and its an item that can appear in rooms, have speed and direction, be in combat, etc.
      interface  Scroll
      A scroll is a piece of paper upon which magical spells are written.
      interface  Shield
      A shield is a large flat item useful for blocking melee attacks.
      interface  ShipEngine
      A ShipEngine is a special TechComponent that is often a fuel consumer, and which has special tracked attributes related to its ability to propel a ship and, usually, consume fuel.
      interface  ShipWarComponent
      A ship war component can be a gun or a shield generator.
      interface  Software
      Software is a plain technical item that monitors and manipulates other space ship components and systems, while also managing a user interface for players/mobs monitoring the software.
      interface  SpaceShip
      A Space Ship, which is a space object that's dockable and can change direction.
      interface  SpellHolder
      A spell holder is an item that can contain spells for use in some way, such as a scroll, staff, wand, pills, potions, etc.
      interface  TechComponent
      A TechComponent is a type of electronics item that must be installed into a panel that can accept it.
      interface  Technical
      This is the base class for all tech items.
      interface  Wand
      A wand is an item containing a magic spell that can be invoked on a target, by holding the wand, and then saying the magic word to the target.
      interface  Weapon
      An item that can be used to do damage to another mob.
      interface  Wearable

      Subinterfaces of CMObject in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Libraries.interfaces 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  AbilityComponents
      Library for configureing and managing the rules for what resource components (magic dust, tools, etc) are required every time a particular skill is used.
      interface  AbilityMapper
      The Ability Mapper Library handles everything dealing with the relationship between players, races, etc and Abilities (Skills, Spells, Prayers, etc).
      interface  AbilityParameters
      Abilities, like common skills and others, have parameter definition strings that tell the system about any parameters that modify how the ability works.
      interface  AchievementLibrary
      The achievement library forms the basis of the achievement system, which accepts player events as input, as well as the file based achievement definition files, and tracks player and account completion of achievements through trackers.
      interface  AreaGenerationLibrary
      The AreaGenerationLibrary is the random generator, which takes a special flavor of xml as input to randomly generate anything from strings, to mobs and items, whole populated rooms, or entire areas.
      interface  AutoTitlesLibrary
      The library for managing the various auto-titles, which are player titles that can, according to a mask, be automatically added and removed from players as they meet, and stop meeting, various criterium.
      interface  CatalogLibrary
      The Catalog Library maintains the prototypes of various Items and Mobs who are keyed by their Name.
      interface  ChannelsLibrary
      The main chat channels management library.
      interface  CharCreationLibrary
      This library manages everything related to logging a player or account in, creating a character, the account menu, certain login procedures, the rules around player names, start rooms, death rooms, and morgue rooms.
      interface  ClanManager
      This library manages the list of Clans in the game, and helps administer their most basic functions.
      interface  CMFlagLibrary
      The Flag Library is full of shortcut methods for checking the state of objects in a high level way.
      interface  CMLibrary
      This is the base interface for all CoffeeMud libraries.
      interface  CMMiscUtils
      The MiscUtils (Miscellaneous Utilities) library should not exist.
      interface  ColorLibrary
      The color library does just what it says, provides access to methods to translate colors from words, to ansi codes, to html tags, and combine them all in ways appropriate for their use.
      interface  CombatLibrary
      Fighting, healing, determining combatants, death, attacking, damaging, and formations.
      interface  CommonCommands
      Message handlers for the basic common commands, like get, drop, put, etc.
      interface  DatabaseEngine
      Not really much point in saying a lot here.
      interface  DiceLibrary
      The Dice library governs random numbers in various ranges, various hit point generation algorithms, and selecting objects from various lists at random.

      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  Auctioneer
      An Auctioneer is a type of ShopKeeper that wants customers to bid higher prices on items instead of simply buying them.
      interface  Banker
      A Banker is a kind of shopkeeper that belongs to a "chain" which shares access to a common store of player/clan accounts to hold money and items.
      interface  Deity
      A Deity is a type of mob that provides benefits (and punishments) for players that worship them, especially Clerics.
      interface  Librarian
      A Librarian is a kind of shopkeeper that belongs to a "chain" which shares access to a common store of shop items.
      interface  MOB
      A MOB is a creature in the system, from a user down to a goblin.
      interface  PostOffice
      A PostOffice is a kind of shopkeeper that belongs to a "chain" which shares access to a common store of post office boxes to hold items for players.
